InputStream.read:

InputStream.read() is a method in Java's InputStream class that reads a single byte of data from the input stream. It takes one parameter, an integer buffer, which represents the byte to be read. The method returns the actual number of bytes read, or -1 if the end of the stream has been reached.

Example:
```java
InputStream in = new FileInputStream("example.txt");
byte[] buffer = new byte[1024];
int bytesRead = in.read(buffer);
if (bytesRead > 0) {
    // Read data
} else {
    // End of stream reached
}
```
